/* DATA DESCRIPTION:
Citation:	Lisiecki, Lorraine E; Raymo, Maureen E (2005): (Appendix 3) Age model conversions of the SPECMAP and S95 age models to the LR04 age model [dataset]. PANGAEA, https://doi.org/10.1594/PANGAEA.704173, 
	In supplement to: Lisiecki, LE; Raymo, ME (2005): A Pliocene-Pleistocene stack of 57 globally distributed benthic d18O records. Paleoceanography, 20, PA1003, https://doi.org/10.1029/2004PA001071
Other version:	Lisiecki, Lorraine E; Raymo, Maureen E (2005): LR04 Global Pliocene-Pleistocene benthic d18O stack [dataset]. NOAA National Centers for Environmental Information, https://doi.org/10.25921/K88J-0106
Comment:	Conversions to the LR04 age model (this paper, data set: doi:10.1594/PANGAEA.701576) from the S95 composite age model (Sites V19-30, 677, and 846; Shackleton, 1995) and the SPECMAP stack (Imbrie et al., 1984). AGE gives the ages of the S95 and SPECMAP stack
Parameter(s):	AGE [ka BP] (Age) * GEOCODE
	Age model [ka] (Age model) * PI: Lisiecki, Lorraine E (https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7859-0096, lelisi@ucsb.edu, http://lorraine-lisiecki.com/) * COMMENT: LR04 converted to S95 ages model
	Age model, optional [ka] (Age model opt) * PI: Lisiecki, Lorraine E (https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7859-0096, lelisi@ucsb.edu, http://lorraine-lisiecki.com/) * COMMENT: LR04 converted to SPECMAP stack
License:	Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported (CC-BY-3.0) (URI: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/)
Size:	6094 data points
*/
